SIMPLE: mountainous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mountainous
<hw>Moun"tain*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>montagneux</ets>, L. <ets>montaniosus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of, or containing, mountains; <as>as, the <ex>mountainous</ex>
country of the Swiss</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inhabiting mountains.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Large as, or resembling, a mountain; huge; of great
bulk; <as>as, a <ex>mountainous</ex> heap</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mountainousness</ent>⟦br⟧
